def blur_img(img):
    return scipy.ndimage.gaussian_filter(img, 2)

def remove_small_items(binary_mask, x=15, y=15):
    eroded_mask = scipy.ndimage.binary_erosion(binary_mask,
                                               structure=np.ones((x, y))).astype(binary_mask.dtype)
    recon_mask = scipy.ndimage.binary_propagation(eroded_mask,
                                                  mask=binary_mask)
    return recon_mask

def get_red(img):
    return img[:,:,0]

def get_green(img):
    return img[:,:,1]

def get_blue(img):
    return img[:,:,2]

def red_mask(red_lay, green_lay, blue_lay):
    # print('Red mask')
    test1 = red_lay > 50
    if np.any(test1):
        test2 = np.less(np.clip(green_lay.astype('uint16') * 1.5, 0, 255), red_lay)
        test3 = np.less(np.clip(blue_lay.astype('uint16') * 1.5, 0, 255), red_lay)
        red_m = test1 & test2 & test3
        mask_red = remove_small_items(red_m)
    else:
        mask_red = np.zeros(red_lay.shape, dtype='bool')
    return mask_red

def blue_mask(red_lay, green_lay, blue_lay):
    # print('Blue mask')
    test1 = blue_lay > 39
    if np.any(test1):
        # Remove divide by 0 errors
        blue_lay[blue_lay==0] = 1
        green_ratio = (green_lay / blue_lay)
        test2 = (green_ratio < 1) & (green_ratio > 0.5)
        test3 = (red_lay / blue_lay) < 1.1
        blue_m = test1 & test2 & test3
        mask_blue = remove_small_items(blue_m)

    else:
        mask_blue = np.zeros(blue_lay.shape, dtype='bool')
    return mask_blue

def green_mask(red_lay, green_lay, blue_lay):
    # print('Green mask')
    test1 = green_lay > 60
    if np.any(test1):
        # Remove divide by 0 errors
        green_lay[green_lay==0] = 1
        red_ratio = (red_lay / green_lay)
        test2 = (red_ratio < 1) & (red_ratio > 0.15)
        test3 = (blue_lay / green_lay) < 0.91
        green_m = test1 & test2 & test3
        mask_green = remove_small_items(green_m)
    else:
        mask_green = np.zeros(green_lay.shape, dtype='bool')
    return mask_green

def create_img(out_shape, redm, greenm, bluem):
    cvzero_img = np.zeros(out_shape, dtype=int)
    cvzero_img[redm==True] = [255, 0, 0]
    cvzero_img[greenm==True] = [0, 255, 0]
    cvzero_img[bluem==True] = [0, 0, 255]
    return cvzero_img

plt.axis('off')
f, ax = plt.subplots(len(images), 5, figsize=(12,36))
plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0, hspace=1.02, top=1.99, bottom=0.01, left=0.01, right=0.99)
# Step through test images and display mask for each colour
img_timing = []
for row, this_img in enumerate(images):
    process_start = time.perf_counter()
    red_c = get_red(this_img)
    green_c = get_green(this_img)
    blue_c = get_blue(this_img)
    rm = red_mask(red_c, green_c, blue_c)
    bm = blue_mask(red_c, green_c, blue_c)
    gm = green_mask(red_c, green_c, blue_c)
    img_timing.append(time.perf_counter() - process_start)
    ax[row][0].set_title(row)
    ax[row][0].imshow(this_img)
    ax[row][1].set_title('red mask')
    ax[row][1].imshow(np.invert(rm), cmap='gray', vmin=0,vmax=1)
    # ax[row][1].imshow(np.invert(red_c), cmap='gray')
    ax[row][2].set_title('green mask')
    ax[row][2].imshow(np.invert(gm), cmap='gray', vmin=0,vmax=1)
    # ax[row][2].imshow(np.invert(green_c), cmap='gray')
    ax[row][3].set_title('blue mask')
    ax[row][3].imshow(np.invert(bm), cmap='gray', vmin=0,vmax=1)
    # ax[row][3].imshow(np.invert(blue_c), cmap='gray')
    ax[row][4].set_title('Composite')
    ax[row][4].imshow(create_img(this_img.shape, rm, gm, bm))

print('Min: {}, Max: {}, Mean: {}'.format(min(img_timing), 
                                          max(img_timing), 
                                          sum(img_timing) / len(img_timing)))
plt.show()
